[{"text": "Translator: Joseph Geni\nReviewer: Morton Bast", "start": 0.0, "duration": 7.0}, {"text": "Everyone is both a learner", "start": 16.395, "duration": 1.976}, {"text": "and a teacher.", "start": 18.371, "duration": 1.512}, {"text": "This is me being inspired", "start": 19.883, "duration": 2.456}, {"text": "by my first tutor,", "start": 22.339, "duration": 1.191}, {"text": "my mom,", "start": 23.53, "duration": 0.945}, {"text": "and this is me teaching", "start": 24.475, "duration": 2.623}, {"text": "Introduction to Artificial Intelligence", "start": 27.098, "duration": 1.953}, {"text": "to 200 students", "start": 29.051, "duration": 1.24}, {"text": "at Stanford University.", "start": 30.291, "duration": 1.272}, {"text": "Now the students and I", "start": 31.563, "duration": 1.456}, {"text": "enjoyed the class,", "start": 33.019, "duration": 1.176}, {"text": "but it occurred to me", "start": 34.195, "duration": 1.416}, {"text": "that while the subject matter", "start": 35.611, "duration": 1.711}, {"text": "of the class is advanced", "start": 37.322, "duration": 1.289}, {"text": "and modern,", "start": 38.611, "duration": 0.688}, {"text": "the teaching technology isn't.", "start": 39.299, "duration": 2.319}, {"text": "In fact, I use basically", "start": 41.618, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "the same technology as", "start": 43.954, "duration": 2.37}, {"text": "this 14th-century classroom.", "start": 46.324, "duration": 2.63}, {"text": "Note the textbook,", "start": 48.954, "duration": 2.8}, {"text": "the sage on the stage,", "start": 51.754, "duration": 2.944}, {"text": "and the sleeping guy", "start": 54.698, "duration": 1.899}, {"text": "in the back. (Laughter)", "start": 56.597, "duration": 0.901}, {"text": "Just like today.", "start": 57.498, "duration": 2.937}, {"text": "So my co-teacher,", "start": 60.435, "duration": 3.111}, {"text": "Sebastian Thrun, and I thought,", "start": 63.546, "duration": 1.64}, {"text": "there must be a better way.", "start": 65.186, "duration": 1.774}, {"text": "We challenged ourselves", "start": 66.96, "duration": 1.654}, {"text": "to create an online class", "start": 68.614, "duration": 1.291}, {"text": "that would be equal or better", "start": 69.905, "duration": 1.631}, {"text": "in quality to our Stanford class,", "start": 71.536, "duration": 2.336}, {"text": "but to bring it to anyone", "start": 73.872, "duration": 2.21}, {"text": "in the world for free.", "start": 76.082, "duration": 1.63}, {"text": "We announced the class on July 29th,", "start": 77.712, "duration": 2.568}, {"text": "and within two weeks, 50,000 people", "start": 80.28, "duration": 3.209}, {"text": "had signed up for it.", "start": 83.489, "duration": 1.407}, {"text": "And that grew to 160,000 students", "start": 84.896, "duration": 3.105}, {"text": "from 209 countries.", "start": 88.001, "duration": 2.064}, {"text": "We were thrilled to have", "start": 90.065, "duration": 1.808}, {"text": "that kind of audience,", "start": 91.873, "duration": 1.121}, {"text": "and just a bit terrified that we", "start": 92.994, "duration": 2.639}, {"text": "hadn't finished preparing the class yet. (Laughter)", "start": 95.633, "duration": 2.311}, {"text": "So we got to work.", "start": 97.944, "duration": 1.612}, {"text": "We studied what others had done,", "start": 99.556, "duration": 1.636}, {"text": "what we could copy and what we could change.", "start": 101.192, "duration": 2.323}, {"text": "Benjamin Bloom had showed", "start": 103.515, "duration": 2.661}, {"text": "that one-on-one tutoring works best,", "start": 106.176, "duration": 1.809}, {"text": "so that's what we tried to emulate,", "start": 107.985, "duration": 2.128}, {"text": "like with me and my mom,", "start": 110.113, "duration": 1.44}, {"text": "even though we knew", "start": 111.553, "duration": 1.505}, {"text": "it would be one-on-thousands.", "start": 113.058, "duration": 1.918}, {"text": "Here, an overhead video camera", "start": 114.976, "duration": 2.201}, {"text": "is recording me as I'm talking", "start": 117.177, "duration": 1.832}, {"text": "and drawing on a piece of paper.", "start": 119.009, "duration": 1.679}, {"text": "A student said, \"This class felt", "start": 120.688, "duration": 2.409}, {"text": "like sitting in a bar", "start": 123.097, "duration": 1.152}, {"text": "with a really smart friend", "start": 124.249, "duration": 1.479}, {"text": "who's explaining something", "start": 125.728, "duration": 1.204}, {"text": "you haven't grasped, but are about to.\"", "start": 126.932, "duration": 2.301}, {"text": "And that's exactly what we were aiming for.", "start": 129.233, "duration": 2.116}, {"text": "Now, from Khan Academy, we saw", "start": 131.349, "duration": 2.788}, {"text": "that short 10-minute videos", "start": 134.137, "duration": 1.824}, {"text": "worked much better than trying", "start": 135.961, "duration": 1.776}, {"text": "to record an hour-long lecture", "start": 137.737, "duration": 2.071}, {"text": "and put it on the small-format screen.", "start": 139.808, "duration": 2.417}, {"text": "We decided to go even shorter", "start": 142.225, "duration": 2.192}, {"text": "and more interactive.", "start": 144.417, "duration": 1.648}, {"text": "Our typical video is two minutes,", "start": 146.065, "duration": 2.247}, {"text": "sometimes shorter, never more", "start": 148.312, "duration": 1.752}, {"text": "than six, and then we pause for", "start": 150.064, "duration": 2.689}, {"text": "a quiz question, to make it", "start": 152.753, "duration": 1.367}, {"text": "feel like one-on-one tutoring.", "start": 154.12, "duration": 1.878}, {"text": "Here, I'm explaining how a computer uses", "start": 155.998, "duration": 2.402}, {"text": "the grammar of English", "start": 158.4, "duration": 1.248}, {"text": "to parse sentences, and here,", "start": 159.648, "duration": 2.177}, {"text": "there's a pause and the student", "start": 161.825, "duration": 2.064}, {"text": "has to reflect, understand what's going on", "start": 163.889, "duration": 2.237}, {"text": "and check the right boxes", "start": 166.126, "duration": 1.64}, {"text": "before they can continue.", "start": 167.766, "duration": 1.417}, {"text": "Students learn best when", "start": 169.183, "duration": 2.448}, {"text": "they're actively practicing.", "start": 171.631, "duration": 1.248}, {"text": "We wanted to engage them, to have them grapple", "start": 172.879, "duration": 2.296}, {"text": "with ambiguity and guide them to synthesize", "start": 175.175, "duration": 2.968}, {"text": "the key ideas themselves.", "start": 178.143, "duration": 1.665}, {"text": "We mostly avoid questions", "start": 179.808, "duration": 1.712}, {"text": "like, \"Here's a formula, now", "start": 181.52, "duration": 1.711}, {"text": "tell me the value of Y", "start": 183.231, "duration": 1.075}, {"text": "when X is equal to two.\"", "start": 184.306, "duration": 1.212}, {"text": "We preferred open-ended questions.", "start": 185.518, "duration": 1.817}, {"text": "One student wrote, \"Now I'm seeing", "start": 187.335, "duration": 3.178}, {"text": "Bayes networks and examples of", "start": 190.513, "duration": 1.862}, {"text": "game theory everywhere I look.\"", "start": 192.375, "duration": 1.568}, {"text": "And I like that kind of response.", "start": 193.943, "duration": 1.738}, {"text": "That's just what we were going for.", "start": 195.681, "duration": 1.806}, {"text": "We didn't want students to memorize the formulas;", "start": 197.487, "duration": 2.194}, {"text": "we wanted to change the way", "start": 199.681, "duration": 1.19}, {"text": "they looked at the world.", "start": 200.871, "duration": 1.09}, {"text": "And we succeeded.", "start": 201.961, "duration": 1.326}, {"text": "Or, I should say, the students succeeded.", "start": 203.287, "duration": 2.4}, {"text": "And it's a little bit ironic", "start": 205.687, "duration": 1.919}, {"text": "that we set about to disrupt traditional education,", "start": 207.606, "duration": 2.913}, {"text": "and in doing so, we ended up", "start": 210.519, "duration": 2.016}, {"text": "making our online class", "start": 212.535, "duration": 1.584}, {"text": "much more like a traditional college class", "start": 214.119, "duration": 2.327}, {"text": "than other online classes.", "start": 216.446, "duration": 1.841}, {"text": "Most online classes, the videos are always available.", "start": 218.287, "duration": 3.215}, {"text": "You can watch them any time you want.", "start": 221.502, "duration": 1.817}, {"text": "But if you can do it any time,", "start": 223.319, "duration": 2.287}, {"text": "that means you can do it tomorrow,", "start": 225.606, "duration": 1.505}, {"text": "and if you can do it tomorrow,", "start": 227.111, "duration": 1.408}, {"text": "well, you may not ever", "start": 228.519, "duration": 2.162}, {"text": "get around to it. (Laughter)", "start": 230.681, "duration": 1.758}, {"text": "So we brought back the innovation", "start": 232.439, "duration": 2.192}, {"text": "of having due dates. (Laughter)", "start": 234.631, "duration": 2.087}, {"text": "You could watch the videos", "start": 236.718, "duration": 1.312}, {"text": "any time you wanted during the week,", "start": 238.03, "duration": 1.912}, {"text": "but at the end of the week,", "start": 239.942, "duration": 1.155}, {"text": "you had to get the homework done.", "start": 241.097, "duration": 1.717}, {"text": "This motivated the students to keep going, and it also", "start": 242.814, "duration": 1.913}, {"text": "meant that everybody was working", "start": 244.727, "duration": 2.856}, {"text": "on the same thing at the same time,", "start": 247.583, "duration": 1.518}, {"text": "so if you went into a discussion forum,", "start": 249.101, "duration": 1.497}, {"text": "you could get an answer from a peer within minutes.", "start": 250.598, "duration": 2.704}, {"text": "Now, I'll show you some of the forums, most of which", "start": 253.302, "duration": 2.939}, {"text": "were self-organized by the students themselves.", "start": 256.241, "duration": 2.766}, {"text": "From Daphne Koller and Andrew Ng, we learned", "start": 259.007, "duration": 3.224}, {"text": "the concept of \"flipping\" the classroom.", "start": 262.231, "duration": 1.996}, {"text": "Students watched the videos", "start": 264.227, "duration": 1.295}, {"text": "on their own, and then they", "start": 265.522, "duration": 1.588}, {"text": "come together to discuss them.", "start": 267.11, "duration": 1.71}, {"text": "From Eric Mazur, I learned about peer instruction,", "start": 268.82, "duration": 3.157}, {"text": "that peers can be the best teachers,", "start": 271.977, "duration": 2.624}, {"text": "because they're the ones", "start": 274.601, "duration": 1.432}, {"text": "that remember what it's like to not understand.", "start": 276.033, "duration": 2.848}, {"text": "Sebastian and I have forgotten some of that.", "start": 278.881, "duration": 2.681}, {"text": "Of course, we couldn't have", "start": 281.562, "duration": 2.399}, {"text": "a classroom discussion with", "start": 283.961, "duration": 1.632}, {"text": "tens of thousands of students,", "start": 285.593, "duration": 1.546}, {"text": "so we encouraged and nurtured these online forums.", "start": 287.139, "duration": 3.486}, {"text": "And finally, from Teach For America,", "start": 290.625, "duration": 3.048}, {"text": "I learned that a class is not", "start": 293.673, "duration": 1.481}, {"text": "primarily about information.", "start": 295.154, "duration": 1.496}, {"text": "More important is motivation and determination.", "start": 296.65, "duration": 2.831}, {"text": "It was crucial that the students see", "start": 299.481, "duration": 1.84}, {"text": "that we're working hard for them and", "start": 301.321, "duration": 1.8}, {"text": "they're all supporting each other.", "start": 303.121, "duration": 1.409}, {"text": "Now, the class ran 10 weeks,", "start": 304.53, "duration": 2.968}, {"text": "and in the end, about half of the 160,000 students watched", "start": 307.498, "duration": 3.911}, {"text": "at least one video each week,", "start": 311.409, "duration": 1.563}, {"text": "and over 20,000 finished all the homework,", "start": 312.972, "duration": 2.693}, {"text": "putting in 50 to 100 hours.", "start": 315.665, "duration": 1.664}, {"text": "They got this statement of accomplishment.", "start": 317.329, "duration": 1.553}, {"text": "So what have we learned?", "start": 318.882, "duration": 2.119}, {"text": "Well, we tried some old ideas", "start": 321.001, "duration": 2.816}, {"text": "and some new and put them together,", "start": 323.817, "duration": 1.657}, {"text": "but there are more ideas to try.", "start": 325.474, "duration": 2.082}, {"text": "Sebastian's teaching another class now.", "start": 327.556, "duration": 1.814}, {"text": "I'll do one in the fall.", "start": 329.37, "duration": 1.368}, {"text": "Stanford Coursera, Udacity, MITx", "start": 330.738, "duration": 3.76}, {"text": "and others have more classes coming.", "start": 334.498, "duration": 2.271}, {"text": "It's a really exciting time.", "start": 336.769, "duration": 1.488}, {"text": "But to me, the most exciting", "start": 338.257, "duration": 1.472}, {"text": "part of it is the data that we're gathering.", "start": 339.729, "duration": 2.976}, {"text": "We're gathering thousands", "start": 342.705, "duration": 2.696}, {"text": "of interactions per student per class,", "start": 345.401, "duration": 1.656}, {"text": "billions of interactions altogether,", "start": 347.057, "duration": 2.208}, {"text": "and now we can start analyzing that,", "start": 349.265, "duration": 2.504}, {"text": "and when we learn from that,", "start": 351.769, "duration": 1.464}, {"text": "do experimentations,", "start": 353.233, "duration": 1.241}, {"text": "that's when the real revolution will come.", "start": 354.474, "duration": 2.24}, {"text": "And you'll be able to see the results from", "start": 356.714, "duration": 2.776}, {"text": "a new generation of amazing students.", "start": 359.49, "duration": 2.263}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 361.753, "duration": 2.253}]